<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5026-lightbox-title">Agriculture Vault</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>In the early 20th century, all business transactions for the agricultural school were conducted in Agricultural Hall (now Pfendler Hall), built in 1901. The door-sized vault stored cash in the days when the University operated a dairy selling butter, milk, and cream in addition to holding agriculture student records before such files were centralized and digitized.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/28" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden=""></i>See the old agriculture vault in Pfendler Hall.</a></p>
