<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4934-lightbox-title">Big Bertha</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>Brought out for the annual Homecoming game, Big Bertha is an enormous sousaphone that weighs in at well over 50 pounds. Because it’s so cumbersome, it’s at the player’s discretion whether to stand for each song. Leading up to Homecoming, each senior in the tuba section is given a chance to march with Big Bertha during one rehearsal. The largest member of the section has the honor of marching with her for the game. Big Bertha’s been around since the 1940s and is stored in a steamer trunk dubbed the coffin.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FnHawqXEkew&amp;t=17s" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-youtube" aria-hidden=""></i>Watch the &#8220;All-American&#8221; Marching Band practice on Hull Field.</a></p>
