<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>A bell on the 14th fairway of Ackerman-Allen Golf Course memorializes Carl A. Binnie, professor of audiology. Mounted on a brick pedestal at a blind spot in the fairway, the 18-inch Binnie Bell is rung by golfers when it’s clear for the players behind them to play. A plaque describes Binnie as “teacher, scholar, gentleman, and lover of golf.”</p>
