<p> Constructed of metal with a wood tray, bricklayer Phillip Miller manufactured this brick mold under the instructions of John Purdue. The mold was used as a template to shape bricks used in the first two buildings on campus — Purdue Hall, a dormitory for men, and the Science Building, later known as the Pharmacy Building.</p>
