<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5044-lightbox-title">Broken Oar</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> The Purdue Crew student athletic club was established in 1949. Many students who participate in crew have never rowed before joining. This 43 inches of broken oar is displayed in the Levee Boathouse alongside a bevy of trophies. Larry Long (LA’64) recalls an early season practice on March 5, 1983 — “The Wabash at about 20 feet over flood stage, about a mile across including corn fields.” Long encountered resistance with his stroke when the oar snapped. Much to his dismay, a very large pig popped up behind the coxswain. Long’s CliffNotes version: “300 lb. pig loses battle with #4 oar on heavyweight 8 at 20-foot flood stage.”</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/335" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>The broken oar is stored in the Levee Boathouse.</a> </p>
