<p>Dave Vrbanich (MS M’73) constructed the Cary Risk table while he lived at the Quad as a counselor. He built the table in his room, tracing a world map on carbon paper and then transferring the outline to the tabletop before painting the continents. The table was refinished by students in 2004 and continues to reside in the fourth-floor lounge of Cary Southwest.</p>
