<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4974-lightbox-title">Deac&#8217;s Matchbook</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> Horace Reisner (CE’1903) operated Deac’s, a student book and supply store located at 325 State Street in part of the building now occupied by Von’s. Deac’s was the major campus bookstore of the early to mid-20th century. This matchbook was discovered during the renovations of Pappy’s Sweet Shop in 2004. Reisner was the class yell leader in his senior year. He later established the H.G. Reisner Cup, awarded to the winner of an all-campus literary competition.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://goo.gl/maps/qdcZ4j2yBd42" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Deac&#8217;s was located in the Stinespring- Murdock Building, which now houses Von&#8217;s.</a></p>
