<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4954-lightbox-title">The Debris</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>Purdue’s official yearbook, the <em>Debris</em>, was first issued in 1889 and featured early works by John T. McCutcheon (S’89, HDR LA’26), who became known as the Dean of American Cartoonists. His political cartoons earned him a Pulitzer Prize in 1932. McCutcheon named the yearbook Debris on the erroneous belief that “debris” was French for “a collection of works.” The final edition was published in 2008.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/19" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden=""></i>Thumb through copies of the Debris yearbook in Morse Library at the Dauch Alumni Center.</a></p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://earchives.lib.purdue.edu/cdm/search/collection/debris/searchterm/debris/field/all/mode/all/conn/and/order/title" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-link" aria-hidden=""></i>Explore digital copies of the Debris yearbook in the e-Archives.</a></p>
</div>
