<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4959-lightbox-title">Earhart&#8217;s Leather Helmet</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>Worn by Amelia Earhart on her 1932 solo Atlantic flight, this leather helmet is part of the George Palmer Putnam Collection of Earhart Papers at the Purdue Archives. Purdue is home to the world’s largest, most comprehensive collection of Earhart-related papers, memorabilia, and artifacts.</p>
