<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4958-lightbox-title">Edward Harper&#8217;s Drawing Tools</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>Any engineering student of the 19th century would own a set of drawing tools for mechanical drafting. This set belonged to Edward R. Harper of Goshen, Indiana, a member of the class of 1892. As a student, he was literary editor for the <em>Exponent</em>, art editor for the Debris, and president of the Irving Literary Society. The first student organization on campus, the society was devoted to the intellectual pursuit of literature and debate. Harper died of tuberculosis 16 days before graduation.</p>
