<p> A relatively recent addition to the collegian wardrobe, game-day bib overalls made their splash on campus when the Reamers began wearing them en masse during athletic events. Their popularity continues to increase, with more and more students donning striped bibs every home football game. Although the bibs are manufactured in a variety of school color combinations, the attire seems especially appropriate for an engineering school with a train mascot, hearkening back to the conductor overalls of yesteryear. </p>
</div>
