<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5008-lightbox-title">George Ade&#8217;s Table</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> This round oak table housed in Wood Hall reportedly came from Hazeldon, the home of George Ade (S’1887, HDR LA’26). Ade, at one time one of the most famous writers in the country, often focused on current events in his sharp, satirical humor.</p>
