<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4965-lightbox-title">Glee Club Jazz Band Photo</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>In the 1920s, when the United States was experiencing the Jazz Age, the Purdue Varsity Glee Club developed its own Jazz Band. The 1922 <em>Debris</em> describes the Jazz Band as a novelty, but the prominence of the Jazz Band and the separate Saxophone Sextette at Glee Club performances showed the University’s connection to one of the iconic components of the Roaring ’20s culture.</p>
