<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4937-lightbox-title">Gold and Black Cross</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> The Purdue Memorial Union was built as a permanent memorial to the 4,080 Boilermakers who served in World War I. Construction was largely funded through student and alumni donations. The gold and black cross on the floor of the Great Hall honors the 67 Purdue men who gave their lives for their country in the Great War. It has since been extended to honor all Purdue faithful who lost their lives in service to the United States of America.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/235" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Pay tribute to Purdue&#8217;s servicemen and women in the Great Hall of Purdue Memorial Union</a>. </p>
</div>
