<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4969-lightbox-title">Griffin Hatpin</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>This hatpin, dating from 1895, features the University’s third seal and the first to use a winged griffin, slanted shield, and uncial lettering — elements used in each successive redesign. According to the <em>Purdue Crest</em> by Michael Horoho (LA’93), the design was created by Abby Phelps Lytle, then head of the art department. The aesthetically pleasing design was difficult to reproduce clearly and was retired after 15 years.</p>
