<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>After 55 years in storage, the clock that once adorned the second Heavilon Hall, then home to Purdue engineering, was restored and installed in the atrium of the Mechanical Engineering Building’s Gatewood Wing in 2011. The clock is displayed in full working condition with its original nine-foot pendulum.</p>
