<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4953-lightbox-title">John Purdue&#8217;s Death Mask</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> John Purdue died of an apparent stroke on September 12, 1876, the first day of classes of the University’s third academic year. University trustees paid local dentist Anderson M. Moore $25 to cast a death mask of Purdue from plaster to be referenced in the creation of a statue, stating, “a handsome monument will ere long mark Mr. Purdue’s grave on the university grounds.” The mask was stored in a First National Bank vault. A statue of Purdue was not erected on campus until 2013.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://goo.gl/maps/A1FyAfgjw4o" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Sit beside John Purdue&#8217;s statue on the Memorial Mall</a></p>
