<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5042-lightbox-title">John Purdue&#8217;s Summer Trousers</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> One of the wealthiest businessmen in the state, John Purdue typically wore a black bow tie and white shirt paired with a black vest, suit coat, and pants, though during the summer he would “occasionally” sport white linen trousers purchased in New York City. The waist of the pants is 42 inches and the inseam 30 inches. These trousers, part of the permanent collection at the Tippecanoe County Historical Association, were referenced during the creation of a life-size statue of Purdue to estimate a more accurate depiction of his body size.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://goo.gl/maps/A1FyAfgjw4o" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Sit beside John Purdue&#8217;s statue on the Memorial Mall.</a> </p>
</div>
