<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4915-lightbox-title">John Purdue&#8217;s Top Hat</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>John Purdue was born into poverty on October 31, 1802, in a 360-square-foot log cabin in the Appalachian Mountains of Pennsylvania, where he lived with his parents and nine sisters, one of whom died in infancy. No one could have predicted what lay ahead for him. That one day he would become one of the most successful businessmen in the state of Indiana, sporting this gray felt hat he bought in New York. That he would use his wealth to establish Indiana’s land-grant university. That the name Purdue would be one of eminence, forever synonymous with innovation and progress. For John Purdue, education was the flame that lit the world.</p>
<p><em>John Purdue’s top hat is part of the permanent collection at the Tippecanoe County Historical Association.</em></p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://goo.gl/maps/A1FyAfgjw4o" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden=""></i>Sit beside John Purdue&#8217;s statue on the Memorial Mall</a>.</p>
