<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> Although Purdue is not considered a music school, its students and musical organizations have always had a strong tradition of performing popular music. During the 1880s and 1890s, being able to play the mandolin or Spanish guitar was a strong indicator of one’s sophistication, and being a member of the Mandolin or Guitar Club raised one’s status as a “sophisticated gentleman” on campus. </p>
