<div class="p150-item-detail__content-container">
<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5053-lightbox-title">Phoenix Sundial</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> The sculptural sundial created by David Wesley (AAE’72) while he was an undergraduate was installed on the Memorial Mall in 1972. Wesley enrolled in independent art classes and began working on a model for a sundial in the shape of a bird’s wing. An art professor saw the model and encouraged Wesley to pursue creation of the sundial. He connected Paul Lykoudis (MS ME’54, PhD ME’56), director of the Aerospace Sciences Laboratory, who spearheaded its manufacturing in the wind tunnel shop. The project was funded by the College of Astronautical and Aeronautical Engineering. Sadly, the sweeping wing has been missing for decades, and the sundial no longer functions, although Wesley says he hopes to see it restored.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://goo.gl/maps/ySaRWPwLR962" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>See the Phoenix Sundial on the Memorial Mall.</a> </p>
