<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5040-lightbox-title">Pink Mitten</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> In 1982, Ruth Krauch, an information clerk at the Purdue Memorial Union, was giving a holiday tour to a school group when one of them spotted a pink mitten hanging from a high branch in the Christmas tree. Krauch was inspired to write a story about the origins of the mitten, which she read to visiting children until her retirement. Today, the mitten is still hung in the same spot it was first discovered.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/235" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Visit the Christmas tree in the Great Hall of Purdue Memorial Union.</a> </p>
