<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5019-lightbox-title">President&#8217;s Office Scrapbook</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> This scrapbook from the 1890s contains all manner of correspondence sent to the president’s office pertaining to student life, such as notes about students’ grades or pass/fail status, changes to course of study, and letters of recommendation. Pasted within is this request from John S. Reid: “To the Faculty; Please allow me to change from the electrical course to the agricultural course for special reasons.” There is no record of Reid graduating.</p>
