<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5010-lightbox-title">Punch Cards</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>David A. Studebaker (ME’65) was one of the first students of computer science at Purdue, taking a noncredit Fortran II class in late 1962, around the time the Department of Computer Science was established. It was the first of its kind in the country. Studebaker saved these punch cards from his time as a student worker in the Purdue Computing Center from 1963 to 1965. This particular set prints out an image of Alfred E. Neuman, mascot for <em>Mad Magazine</em>.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/9" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden=""></i>The Department of Computer Science is now housed in Lawson.</a></p>
