<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4972-lightbox-title">Purdue Arena Program</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> The first game ever played in Purdue Arena saw the Boilermakers take on John Wooden (HHS’32, HDR HHS’75) and his top-ranked UCLA team in a classic contest. The Boilermakers came up just short, 73–71, in front of a standing-room-only crowd of more than 14,400 in the debut of the legendary Rick “The Rocket” Mount (-LA’70). The circular concrete and steel structure with a domed roof was hailed as “the first of its kind among collegiate sports facilities.”</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/170" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Visit Mackey Arena.</a> </p>
