<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5017-lightbox-title">R.B. Stewart&#8217;s Briefcase</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p style="text-align: left;">When R.B. Stewart arrived on campus as controller in 1925, enrollment was 3,000 students; the physical plant was worth $3 million; and the endowment totaled $340,000. Upon his retirement as vice president and treasurer in 1961, enrollment had grown to 22,000; the physical plant was valued at $160 million; and yields from the $25 million endowment were producing funds for research, scholarships, and grants. One of the University’s most influential administrators, Stewart had a domineering and formidable personality. A colleague once said, “He was an interesting person to work for, but it was much better if your ideas and his coincided.”</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/360" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Stewart Center is named for R.B. Stewart.</a></p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.lib.purdue.edu/spcol" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-tag" aria-hidden></i>Explore the Archives</a> </p>
