<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5029-lightbox-title">Skull &#038; Crescent Paddle</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> Steve Epner (S’71, MS T’07) was inducted into Skull &amp; Crescent sophomore honorary society in 1968. As part of his pledge period, he had to visit the local butcher shop to retrieve a bone and then clean, bleach, and decorate it. He carried the bone around campus asking sorority members to sign. Each signature was then coated in clear nail polish so it would not rub off.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/19" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Steve Epner&#8217;s Skull &amp; Crescent paddle is on display in the Rudolph Room at Dauch Alumni Center.</a> </p>
