<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4991-lightbox-title">Smokestack</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> The 1924 power plant with its 250-foot-high smokestack was a technological marvel at the time it was built. The building — which later acquired the name Heating and Power Plant-North — was the sole generator of heat and power on campus. The looming tower was a visible marker on a campus closely surrounded by farm fields in all directions. After the power plant was decommissioned in the 1980s, the smokestack took on the nostalgic role of a historic landmark. The smokestack was disassembled in 1992, but the power plant sat mostly unused for another 25 years. This image was taken just before the power plant was demolished in 2014.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/316" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>See this image of the smokestack and other historic images from the power plant in the Wilmeth Active Learning Center.</a> </p>
