<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> The smoking fence got its name from 19th-century students skirting a rule that forbade smoking on campus. An iron-rail fence encircled much of the main campus, keeping cattle from nearby pastures from roaming the grounds. Students would congregate along the fence for a smoke, leaning over the fence to be technically off campus.</p>
