<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> PSUB (Purdue Student Union Board) debuted its first madrigal dinner in 1979. The comedic Renaissance-themed dinner theater featured a feast of several courses, each heralded with a traditional song. Roving costumed actors entertained guests throughout the evening. This peacock, stuffed by Larry’s Taxidermy in Wingate, Indiana, served as a prop for a dinner in the late ’80s. The events were phased out by the mid-’90s. </p>
