<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4940-lightbox-title">Sweet Shop Coke Cup</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> When the Purdue Memorial Union opened in 1924, its dining facilities consisted of a cafeteria with a soda fountain and banquet service, all operating as one unit. The first true Sweet Shop appeared in its own separate space in 1927 and was expanded to its present size in 1957. Many Sweet Shop Coke dates developed into romances under the happy guidance of Frank “Pappy” Fox, manager of the Sweet Shop from 1927 to 1959. Pappy claimed that in 1938, the Sweet Shop was the largest independent dispenser of Coca-Cola in the United States. This vintage cup was discovered during the shop’s most recent renovation in 2004.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://collections.lib.purdue.edu/campus/buildings/235" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden></i>Sip a Coke at Pappy&#8217;s Sweet Shop in Purdue Memorial Union</a>.</p>
