<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="4985-lightbox-title">Tribute to David Ross Book</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p>In 1938, the Purdue Alumni Association commissioned a book to honor David Ross (ME’1893), one of the University’s most influential benefactors. The book was a convergence of Purdue legends. It was designed by acclaimed book designer and typographer Bruce Rogers (S’1890, HDR LA’32) and included a frontispiece by Pulitzer Prize-winning political cartoonist John McCutcheon (S’1889, HDR LA’26). Rogers and McCutcheon worked together on the Debris yearbook as students. In the illustration, Ross is depicted seated at a desk with portraits of John Purdue, Edward Elliott (HDR E’47), and Amelia Earhart in the background.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://goo.gl/maps/QMZM92XLa8G2" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-map-marker" aria-hidden=""></i>David Ross is buried at the top of Slayter Hill.</a></p>
<p><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.lib.purdue.edu/spcol" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-tag" aria-hidden=""></i>Explore the Archives</a></p>
</div>
