<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5006-lightbox-title">Water Tower</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> For decades, the campus water tower was the scourge of the West Lafayette skyline. At 142 feet tall, the tower was originally painted red and white to comply with FAA regulations. Finally, in 2001, the FAA made an exception, granting the University permission to repaint the water tower with the school’s logo and colors.</p>
