<p> WBAA, the oldest continuously operating radio station in Indiana, was licensed in 1922. Its first broadcast covered Arbor Day and aired at 9:00 p.m. on April 21, 1922. Then housed in the Electrical Engineering Building, the station moved to studios in the newly opened Hall of Music in 1940.</p>
