<h3 class="p150-item-detail__title" id="5002-lightbox-title">Women&#8217;s Athletic Association Patch</h3>
<div class="p150-item-detail__description">
<p> From the collection of Rosemary Anne Murphy (S’29), one of Purdue’s first prominent women athletes. During her undergraduate years, she played soccer, basketball, and baseball and participated in coed track meets, although women had no intercollegiate competition at that time. In 1927, Murphy became the president of the Women’s Athletic Association. She traveled to New York to represent the University at the Athletic Conference of American College Women.</p>
